Instructions:
- Keep the final response concise (no more than 8 sentences)
- Maintain factual accuracy grounded in the provided content
- Preserve key terminology and proper nouns
- Use neutral, third-person voice
- You MUST cite each factual claim by placing [N] at the end of the sentence, where N is the passage number. Example: The system supports full-text search [1].
- Place each citation inline with the sentence it supports. Do NOT group all citations at the end. If multiple passages support a claim, list them: [1][3].

Provide the updated summary only. Do not mention that you performed a refinement.
